<LP>
   COLUMBUS, Ohio -- M/I Schottenstein Homes Inc. said
shareholders approved the previously announced buy-out by a
family trust for $7.50 a share.
   The residential developer said Irving and Melvin
Schottenstein and their family trusts, which own 80% of the
company, will acquire the remaining 20%, or 1,055,000 shares.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The value of the share-purchase is about $7.9 million. The
company, which has acted as a financial adviser to the
Schottensteins, will provide about $2.3 million, and the
Schottenstein families will fund the remaining $5.6 million,
the company said.
