<HL>
   Initial State Jobless Claims
   Increased in June 16 Week
</HL>
<DATE>
06/29/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2
</SO>
<CO>
   LABOR
</CO>
<IN>
ECONOMIC NEWS (ECO)
ECONOMIC AND MONETARY INDICATORS (EMI)
</IN>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- Initial claims for regular state
unemployment benefits rose to a seasonally adjusted 359,000
in the week ended June 16 from 356,000 in the previous week,
the Labor Department said.
   The number of people receiving regular state benefits in
the week ended June 9 was a seasonally adjusted 2,472,000, or
2.4% of those covered by unemployment insurance, up from
2,390,000 in the previous week, when the insured unemployment
rate was 2.3%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Counting all state and federal benefit programs, the
number of people receiving unemployment benefits in the week
ended June 9 fell to 2,253,200 from 2,269,900 a week earlier.
These figures aren't seasonally adjusted.
</TEXT>
