<LP>
   DETROIT -- The 10 major U.S. auto makers planned to build
143,912 cars this week, a 16% increase from 124,013 built a
year ago.
   Chrysler Corp. said its Toledo, Ohio, assembly plant will
halt production for four weeks beginning July 2 "due to
vacation." During the four weeks, about 4,700 hourly workers
will be idled. The plant will resume production July 30.
</LP>
