   Ford Motor Co. said its assembly plants will be idled the
weeks of July 2 and July 9 for the auto maker's traditional
summer break.
   All production facilities will be closed for the July
Fourth holiday.
   General Motors Corp. said it has planned daily overtime at
its assembly plant in Janesville, Wis., which builds the
Chevrolet Cavalier.
