<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- The Federal Communications Commission
disbarred Thomas Root, the lawyer who gained national
attention a year ago when his small plane mysteriously
crashed into the ocean off the Bahamas and he was found with
a gunshot wound.
   The FCC gave Mr. Root until July 6 to end his FCC
practice. Mr. Root, who didn't challenge his disbarment, had
