<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- The Securities and Exchange Commission said
a former Robinson-Humphrey Co. broker settled charges that he
violated securities laws by defrauding at least 18
professional football players.
   Without admitting or denying guilt, Oscar Ayala, now a
salesman at the Shearson Lehman Hutton Inc. unit in Marietta,
