   Steelmaker Plans to Acquire
   Two Pennsylvania Properties
</HL>
<DATE>
06/29/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4
</SO>
<CO>
   NSS MDR
</CO>
<IN>
OIL EQUIPMENT AND SERVICES (OIE)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   NS Group Inc. said it entered a into a letter of intent
with Ambridge Tube Corp., Houston, to acquire the Koppel
Steel Works and Ambridge Rolling Mills facilities. Terms
weren't disclosed.
   The Newport, Ky., steelmaker said the facilities were
formerly operated by the Tubular Products Division of Babcock
&amp; Wilcox, an operating unit of McDermott International Inc.
In January, Babcock &amp; Wilcox entered into a definitive
agreement to sell the facilities to Ambridge Tube.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The Koppel facility, located in Koppel, Pa., contains a
melt shop installed in 1985 and has the capacity to produce
400,000 tons of steel products annually. The Ambridge
facility, located in nearby Ambridge, Pa., contains a
tube-making facility installed in 1976 designed to make
specialty tubing including bearing, mechanical, pressure and
oil country tubing. Both facilities were idled in 1988.
   The acquisition would allow NS to expand its tubular and
bar markets.
