<IN>
PULP, PAPER, PACKAGING (ALL TYPES) (PUL)
</IN>
<LP>
   Stone Container Corp., Chicago, said it opened an expanded
operation costing $24 million at the paper and packaging
company's paper mill in Uncasville, Conn.
   It said the operation will recycle 144,000 tons annually
of used corrugated boxes to be collected from the New York
City and other metropolitan areas in five Northeastern
states.
</LP>
