   In the expansion, part of a $200 million program to
increase Stone's recycling capacity, the plant will make
recycled paper for new boxes. Stone said 16 of its 24 mills
world-wide purchase and recycle about two million tons of
used corrugated boxes and newspapers annually, and an
official said that "by 1992, we'll be consuming three million
tons" a year.
